  "description": "This dataset comprises behavioral and neuroimaging data from two reversal learning tasks designed to investigate differential neural processing of reward gain and punishment avoidance. Participants completed parallel tasks using distinct reinforcers: monetary reward/non-reward and threat avoidance/application of aversive noise stimuli. The punishment task employed individually titrated white noise bursts to equate subjective value with monetary incentives, enabling direct comparison of learning mechanisms across motivational domains.",
